{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> αἴτι-ος</b>, α, ον, <br /> more rarely ος, ον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 547: (see. αἰτία)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:— <b>culpable, responsible</b>, ἐπεὶ οὔ τί μοι αἴτιοί εἰσιν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 1.153, compare 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus 10.34, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.214\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>comparative</i> αἰτιώτερος[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.20: _superlative_, τοὺς αἰτιωτάτους\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>the most guilty</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.50; αἰ. τινος [prev. author] 3.52. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <i>substantive</i>, αἴτιος, ὁ, <b>the accused, the culprit</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 70, etc.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; οἱ αἴ. τοῦ πατρός <b>they who have sinned against</b> my father, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 273\">Refs</a>]:—with <i>genitive</i> <i>of things</i>, οἱ αἴ. τοῦ φόνου[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 117, compare 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 590, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.200. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>responsible for</b>, with <i>genitive</i> <i>of things</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.1, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; αἴτιός τινός τινι being <b>the cause of</b> a thing <b>to</b> a person, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 13.57, compare 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 23.54, 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 8.100\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>infinitive</i>, αἴ. τὸν ἠέρα ξηρὸν εἶναι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.26; τοῦ μὴ φαλακροῦσθαι [prev. author] 3.12, etc.; αἴ. θανεῖν 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 1173; αἰ. πεμφθῆναι ἄγγελον 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 5.23, compare 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 13.82; αἴτιος τὸ σὲ ἀποκρίνασθαι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Laches” 190e\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>comparative</i>, τοῦ.. ἐλευθέραν εἶναι.. αἰτιώτερον[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 24.5, compare 51.21: _superlative_ αἰτιώτατος, ἐν τῷ στενῷ ναυμαχῆσαι\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] <b>mainly instrumental in causing</b> the sea-fight, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.74; αἰ. τοῦ μὴ ἀποθανεῖν 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 20.42; -ώτατόν τι καὶ τελέως δραστικόν 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “D.” 1.23. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> αἴτιον, τό, <b>cause</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἀρχαίης ἰητρικῇς” 6 (_plural_), 21, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.125, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Aulidensis” 939, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.26, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τί ποτ᾽ οὖν ἐστι τὸ αἴτιον τό.. μηδένα εἰπεῖ; [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 8.56; frequently in Philos., τὸ δ᾽ αἴ. τούτου εἶναι ὅτι.. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 11oe, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0159","accentedUnicode":"αἴτιος","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0154","matchingForm":"αἰτέω","stepTransliteration":"aiteō","gloss":"to ask","_zh_tw_Gloss":"求","_es_Gloss":"pedir ","_zh_Gloss":"求"},{"strongNumber":"G0159","matchingForm":"αἴτιος","stepTransliteration":"aitios","gloss":"causer","_zh_tw_Gloss":"根源","_es_Gloss":"el que causa ","_zh_Gloss":"根源"},{"strongNumber":"G0338","matchingForm":"ἀναίτιος","stepTransliteration":"anaitios","gloss":"innocent","_zh_tw_Gloss":"無罪","_es_Gloss":"inocente","_zh_Gloss":"无罪"}],"shortDef":"causer-","mediumDef":"causer, the originator of","stepGloss":"causer","stepTransliteration":"aitios","count":5,"_es_Definit